## Section introduction
* Amazon S3 is one of the main building blocks of AWS
* it's advertised as "infinitely [无限地] scaling" storage
* many websites use Amazon S3 as a backbone [骨干]
* many AWS services use Amazon S3 as an integration [集成] as well
# Amazon S3 

## Use cases

* backup and storage
* disaster recovery
* archive [存档]
* hybrid cloud storage
* application hosting
* media hosting
* data lakes & big data analytics
* software delivery [交付]
* static website
## Buckets [桶]

* Amazon S3 allows people to store objects( files ) in "buckets"(directories)
* buckets must have a **globally unique name (across all regions all accounts)**
* buckets are defined at the region level
* S3 looks like a global service but buckets are created in a region
* Naming convention [约定]
    * No uppercase,No underscore
    * 3-63 characters long
    * Not an IP
    * Must start with lowercase letter or number
    * must NOT start with the prefix [前缀]**xn--**
    * must NOT end with the suffix [后缀] **-s3alias**
## Objects

![图片](data:image/png;base64,)


* Objects (files) have a Key
* the **key**is the FULL path:
    * s3://my-bucket/**my_file.txt**
    * s3://my-bucket/**my_folder1/another_folder/my_file.txt**
* the key is composed [组成] of prefix + object name
    * s3://my-bucket/my_folder1/another_folder/my_file.txt
* there's no concept [概念] of "directories" within buckets (although the UI will trick [欺骗] you to think otherwise)
* just keys with very long names that contain slashes  [斜线]("/")
### Objects (cont)

* Object values are the content of the body :
    * Max,Object Size is 5TB (5000GB)
    * if uploading more than 5GB, must use "multi-part upload"
* Metadata (list of text key / value pairs - system or user metadata)
* Tags (Unicode key / value pair - up to 10) - useful for security / lifecycle
* Version ID (if versioning is enabled)
## Security

Explicit DENY in an IAM Policy will take precedence over an S3 bucket policy.

* **User-Based**
    * **IAM Policies** - which API calls should be allowed for a specific user from IAM
* **Resource-Based**
    * **Bucket Policies** - bucket wide rules from the S3 console - allows cross account
    * **Object Access Control List (ACL)** - finer [更细] grain (can be disabled)
    * **Bucket Access Control List (ACL)** - less common [不常见] (can be disabled)
* **Note ：** an IAM principal [首长] can access an S3 object if
    * the user IAM permissions ALLOW it OR the resource policy ALLOWS it
    * AND there's no explicit [明确的] DENY
* **Encryption**: encrypt objects in Amazon S3 using encryption keys
### S3 Bucket Policies

![图片](data:image/png;base64,)


* JSON based policies
    * Resourece : bucket and objects
    * Effect :  Allow / Deny
    * Actions: set of API to Allow or Deny
    * Principal : the account or user to apply the policy to
* Use S3 bucket for policy to:
    * Grant [授予] public access to the bucket
    * force objects to be encrypted at upload
    * grant access to another account **(Cross Account)**

## Static Website Hosting

![图片](data:image/png;base64,)


* S3 can host [托管] static websites and have them accessible on the Internet
* the website URL will be (depending on the region)
    * http://bucket-name.s3-website-aws-region.amazonaws.com
OR

    * http://bucket-name.s3-website.aws-region.amazonaws.com
* if you get a **403 Forbidden** error, make sure the bucket policy allows public reads
## Versioning

![图片](data:image/png;base64,)


* you can version your file in Amazon S3
* it is enabled at the**bucket level**
* same key overwrite will change the "version" :1,2,3...
* it is best practice to version your buckets
    * protect against unintended [无意的] deletes [防止意外删除] (ability to restore a version)
    * easy to roll back to previous version
* Notes:
    * any file that is not versioned prior to enabling versioning will have version "null"
    * suspending [暂停] versioning does not delete the previous versions
## Replication [复制] (CRR & SRR)

![图片](data:image/png;base64,)


* **Must enable Versioning** in source and destination buckets
* **Cross-Region Replication (CRR)**
* **Same-Region Replication (SRR)**
* buckets can be in different AWS accounts
* copying is asynchronous
* Must give proper [正确的] IAM permissions to S3
* Use cases :
    * **CRR**- compliance [合规性],lower latency access,replication across accounts
    * **SRR**- log aggregation [日志聚合 ] , live replication  [实时复制] between production and test accounts
### Notes

* after you enable Replication, only new objects are replicated
* Optionally, you can replicate existing objects using **S3 Batch Replication**
    * replicates existing objects and objects that failed replication
* for DELETE operations
    * **can replicate delete markers [标记]** from source to target (optional setting)
    * deletions with a version ID are not replicated (to avoid malicious [恶意的] deletes)
* **there is no "chaining" of replication**
    * if bucket 1 has replication into bucket 2, which has replication into bucket 3
    * then objects created in bucket 1 are not replicated to bucket 3
# S3 Storage Classes

* Amazon S3 Standard - General Purpose [一般用途]
* Amazon S3 Standard-Infrequent Access (IA)
* Amazon S3 One Zone-Infrequent Access
* Amazon S3 Glacier Instant [立刻的] Retrieval [恢复]
* Amazon S3 Glacier Flexible Retrieval
* Amazon S3 Glacier Deep Archive [存档]
* Amazon S3 Intelligent Tiering [智能分层]
* can move between classes manually [手动] or using S3 Lifecycle configurations
## S3 Standard - General Purpose

* 99.99% Availability
* Used for frequently accessed data
* low latency and high throughput
* sustain [维持] 2 concurrent [并发] facility [设施] failures
* Use Cases : big Data analytics. mobile & gaming application, content distribution...
## Infrequent Access

* for data that is less frequently accessed ,but requires rapid [迅速] access when needed 
* lower cost than S3 standard
* **Amazon S3 Standard-Infrequent Access (S3 Standard-IA)**
    * 99.9% Availability
    * Use case: Disaster Recovery, backups
* **Amazon S3 One Zone-Infrequent Access (S3 One Zone-IA)**
    * high durability (99.9999999%) in a single AZ;data lost when AZ is destroyed
    * 99.5% availability
    * Use Cases: Storing secondary [次要] backup copies of on-premise [本地] data, or data you can recreate
## Amazon S3 Glacier Storage Classes

* low-cost object storage meant for archiving / backup
* pricing : price fo storage + object retrieval cost
* **Amazon S3 Glacier Instant Retrieval [检索]**
    * millisecond retrieval, great for data accessed once a quarter [季度]
    * minimum storage duration [期限] of 90 days
* **Amazon S3 Glacier Flexible Retrieval**(formerly [以前] Amazon S3 Glacier)
    * expedited [加急] (1 to 5 minutes), Standard (3 to 5 hours), Bulk [批量] (5 to 12 hours) -free
    * minimum storage duration of 90 days
* **Amazon S3 Glacier Deep Archive - for long term [长期] storage :**
    * Standard (12 hours),bulk (48 hours)
    * minimum storage duration of 180 days
## S3 Intelligent -Tiering

* small monthly [每月] monitoring and auto-tiering fee
* move objects automatically between Access Tiers based on usage
* there are no retrieval charges in S3 Intelligent-Tiering
* *frequent access tier (automatic):* default tier
* *infrequent access tier (automatic):* object not accessed for 30 days
* *archive instant access tier (automatic):* object not accessed for 90 days
* *archive access tier(optional) :* configurable from 90 days to 700+days
* *deep archive access tire (optional):*config. from 180 days to 700+ days

# S3 Durability and Availability

* Durability [持久性]
    * high durability (99.999999%, || 9's) of objects across multiple AZ
    * if you store 1000000 objescts with Amazon S3, you can on average expect to incur a  loss of a single object once every 10000 years
    * same for all storage classes
* Availability
    * measures [衡量] how readily available a service is 
    *  varies depending on storage class
    * Example : S3 standard has 99.99% availability = not available 53 minutes a year
